                                    li-Gālīnūs</title>
                            </title>
                            <note> This is a Judaeo-Arabic MS of <persName key="n 80145641"
                                    ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624">Ḥunayn ibn Ishaq</persName>'s
                                Translation of Galen's commentary on the Hippocratic Aphorisms. The
                                beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: 8a; Bk2: 25b; Bk3: 44a;
                                Bk4: 59a; Bk5: 81b; Bk6: 99b. It is incomplete, ending in the middle
                                of comm. on lemma vi. 5.</note>
